@node AMOS "ADB`s Games Volume 3 - AMOS History"

      AMOS is a BASIC programming language created by Francois Lionet
      who, at the time, worked for Mandarin.

      AMOS 1.0 was released for the Amiga in the late 80`s / early 90`s
      and was an instant hit, giving people the ability to do just
      about anything.

      This was followed up by AMOS 1.1 and then AMOS 1.2 (the first
      version I got my hands on) which improved on the previous versions
      by fixing bugs and adding new commands.

      In 1991 AMOS 1.3 was released, which also included a special Object
      Modeller program (or OM for short) which gave people the ability
      to create simple polygon models, with simple "textures".
      Naturally AMOS 1.3 included new commands that allowed you to move,
      rotate and alter the colours of the 3D models.

      In 1992 several new versions of AMOS appeared - Easy AMOS (a
      smaller simplified version, with much fewer commands) and AMOS
      Professional.

      AMOS Professional gave people the ability to develop new commands
      by creating new .LIB files (also known as Extensions). One of the
      famous ones is AMCAF, and a worthy addition too.

      AMOS Professional also included a Compiler which allowed people
      to compile their AMOS Professional programs, making them much
      faster and giving people the ability to create games which could
      run straight from the CLI or from Workbench.
      However, it is as far as I know, not possible to compile programs
      that use commands created from new Extensions (such as AMCAF).

      Several official updates followed (along with some unofficial ones)
      fixing bugs in the previous versions and adding yet more commands
      to AMOS Professional, giving it well over 500 commands


      AMOS Software List:

            AMOS 1.0, 1.1, 1.2 and 1.3 (aka AMOS - The Creator)
            AMOS Professional (often shortened to AMOS Pro)
            AMOS Professional 1.11
            AMOS Professional 1.12
            AMOS Professional 2.0
            AMOS Professional 2.1
            AMOS Professional 2.3
            AMOS Professional 2.X (the best and last version?)

@endnode

@node AMOSfolder "ADB`s Games Volume 3 - AMOS Folder"


      As with Games Volume 2, I have included a bunch of AMOS Pro
      programs. Most of them are not by me, with the source being
      credited at the start of the program.


      3D_lib_hack.AMOS
      ----------------
      A program I wrote last night and finished this morning!
      This allows me to alter the location that AMOS searches for the
      c3d.lib file. In AMOS - The Creator you have 20 characters to play
      with in the 3d.Lib file, but in AMOS Pro you only have 17
      characters in the AMOSPro_3d.Lib file.
      I strongly suggest you take a careful look at the program if you
      wish to alter the location for AMOS - The Creator as it is
      currently setup for the AMOS Pro version.
      You will need to alter the appropriate strings at the start of the
      file before running it for either version though. Also I highly
      suggest you stick to following the original format:

         :APSystem/c3d.lib

      Therefore I changed it to:

         :3DSource/c3d.Lib

      Thus, when running any 3D stuff, it will search for:

         c3d.Lib
         3DSource/c3d.Lib
         :3DSource/c3d.Lib

      and only give an error message if it can't find the c3d.Lib in
      any of those locations.


      If you do use any 3D in your AMOS programs and you used my program
      to change the search path, please mention me somewhere in your
      program.


      3D_Object_mover.AMOS
      --------------------
      A very simple 3D object mover program. Studying the AMOS code helped
      me create the 3D intro for this disk :)


      ADB's_Games2_intro.AMOS
      -----------------------
      The source code for the typewriter intro found on Games Volume 2.


      AF_Pong2.AMOS
      -------------
      Amiga Formats Pong 2 game.


      Border_Flicker.AMOS
      -------------------
      A lame program thats POKEs a byte in memory causing the border to
      flicker slightly!


      guru.AMOS
      ---------
      I have never used this, since I don't believe in using the Guru
      Meditation message box. Kinda cool though.


      HexDump.AMOS
      ------------
      Yes, you can get a Hex dump in AMOS just like you can in Directory
      Opus :)  Useful if you don't have the latter program.


      mouse_colours.AMOS
      ------------------
      Set and/or change the mouse colours.


      mouse_create.AMOS
      -----------------
      Create a mouse image. Use in conjunction with mouse_colours.AMOS


      using_CD32_controller.AMOS
      --------------------------
      I haven't used this in any of my stuff yet, but I can confirm it
      DOES work! :)


      _animated_rainbow.AMOS
      ----------------------
      Err... an animated rainbow :)


      _Mindwarp.AMOS
      --------------
      Probably not a good idea to run this if you suffer from epileptic
      fits. Look at the screen for about 10 seconds and then look at
      the wall.... woah.. spooky man!


      _number_to_speech.AMOS
      ----------------------
      An interesting program that turns numbers in speech properly ;)


      _Strobe_bg_fx.AMOS
      ------------------
      More visual effects.


      _Vmorph2_AF48b.AMOS
      -------------------
      A cool program from Amiga Format disk 48b.
      This takes an image and merges it with a second image. The program
      is slightly buggy in places and unless you have a fast machine
      it will take 30 mins or so to render all 9 frames (full screen),
      even when compiled :(
      It has various options which I haven't really used.


@endnode

@node TextF "ADB's Games Volume 3 - Text Files"

      The "Text Files" folder contains some text files that you may find
      useful or interesting to read.


         AMOSPro_Colours.Lib.s
         ---------------------
         Sourcefile for the AMOS Pro Colours extension. Examine this with
         the other AMOS extension sourcefiles available and you'll have a
         good idea how to put an extension together ;)


         AMOS_bugs
         ---------
         Text file with a list of some of the known AMOS bugs.


         AMOS_Ext_Creation
         -----------------
         A note on how to assemble AMOS Extensions. Other assemblers
         (such as Phx Ass) don't work with normal AMOS Extension source
         code :(


         AMOS_Ext_List
         -------------
         A list of all the known AMOS Extensions for both AMOS - The
         Creator and AMOS Pro. Includes information about all the ones
         I have, plus a full (and hopefully complete) slot list :)


         Console_Notes
         -------------
         A simple text file containing notes on some personal computers
         and videogame consoles of past and present.


@endnode

